@item is_Data
At this address you find the data of the interrupt.

@item is_Code
Address of the interrupt code.  If this address points into RAM, it's
of a different color.

@item NUM
This number represents the type of event the interrupt routine is
called on.  The @samp{IntName} you find in the interrupt detail window
gives you a little bit more information about it.

@strong{Example:} Number 5 means that the interrupt is called at every
vertical blank interval.
@end table


@subheading Actions

