--- like the @code{setpatch} command from Commodore --- patch the
system.

Many viruses patch the system in this way too, but don't panic now.
If you check your system in regular intervals with a current virus
killer, it should be out of danger.

If the whole program code of the library is located in RAM, you will
find a dash (minus sign) here, because in this case it's unimportant
how many jump addresses point into RAM.

